    "updated_at": "2016-01-16T15:40:16Z",
    "body": "I see, thank you for kind answer.\n\nI tried following html with both of `file://` and `http://` protocols. I could reproduce the `font-face` problem. `<p>` tag appears with `MS P Gothic` instead of `Meiryo`. `MS P Gothic` is the default sans-serif font in my Chrome (chrome://settings/fonts).\n\n``` html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"jp_fonts.css\" />\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\">Japanese string, 日本語の文字列</p>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nOS: Windows 10 Pro 64bit JPN\nChrome: 47.0.2526.111 m (64-bit)\n"
  },
